\begin_layout Standard
A second problem starts with the short shrift the conventional historiography
 gives to Cantillon and Quesnay.
 It reveals an important bias in what economic geographers assume land-rent
 theory to be about and a major shortcoming in contemporary land-rent theory.
 Both of them provide macro circular flow flow models in which land rent
 is a central element.
